						               													<description>WaySpotting is an innovative board game for adults and kids who like to spot ways. The game was inspired by the diagrams of Mark Lombardi, and by the idea that every way can be represented by a series of colors, a concept we named WayDNA. At every turn, players try to spot low budget travel routes with two stops and to visit new attractions around the world. They can also use an online companion app to win missions and money. The game has over 10 different types of missions and 1000 trivia questions for all ages. It is an intuitive and fun way to learn about geography, low budget travelling and graph theory concepts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
